Meet Johnny our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Johnny has been kicking it at his comfortable <a href='/home/?user=12x11'>68412-B Wells Road</a> in Golden Valley for a few months now. He moved to Millsberry July 5th, 2008.<br><br>In his short time here, Johnny's managed to score plenty of honors. He's received gold trophies for home run derby, Kai's Surfari, Bumper Boats, and last but not least, Hop and Drop.<br><br>He has been as happy as a pig in mud in the Golden Valley neighborhood. It's just south of the city proper and boasts some of the most scenic locations outside of Millsberry. Of course there is the commute to Millsberry, but Johnny enjoys the occasional bike into town. <br><br>Johnny describes himself as very athletic, a little clever, and creative. With those skills, he just might invent his own brand of competitive sport (and give it a catchy name too). <br><br>His interests include basketball, hunting, and martial arts. Some say they've even seen him karate kick a 3-point shot in while wearing camouflage. He's a legend both on and off the course. <br><br>If you're looking for Johnny your best bet is to check his best friend's house, the Zoo or maybe the tree house. <br><br>If you run into Johnny, make sure you give him a high five and congratulate him on being such an outstanding citizen!<br></div>
